or the door which opens to many Arts:
goldsmithing, building, and more. Indeed,
the seven liberal Arts could not live without her;
for the art of drawing, which embraces all things,
holds all the Arts in her measured bonds.2 The term "matighe stringhen" literally means “moderate strands.” I chose “measured” to echo the double meaning of “measurable” and “moderate.” while “bounds” can refer to the reins of self-control as well as perimeter lines. As Miedema comments, VM is evoking the allegory of self-control. Miedema 425
